.TH "cpuidle_enter" 9 "cpuidle_enter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpuidle_enter \- enter into the specified idle state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cpuidle_enter
.BI "(struct cpuidle_driver *drv "  ","
.BI "struct cpuidle_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
the cpuidle driver tied with the cpu
.IP "dev" 12
the cpuidle device
.IP "index" 12
the index in the idle state table
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the index in the idle state, < 0 in case of error.
The error code depends on the backend driver
